      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — FEA vs. experimental (N=11)",
      "description": "Construct axial stiffness (N/mm) predicted by the FEA ensemble was compared against N=11 physical constructs tested at two independent laboratories following ASTM F1717. Mean experimental stiffness was 187.4 N/mm (CV 4.2%); FEA ensemble mean was 183.9 N/mm, yielding a percent difference of 1.9% — well within the pre-specified 10% acceptance bound. The normalised error metric E/uval = 0.61, satisfying the E/uval < 1.96 criterion. This result was generated during the primary FEA-to-experiment correlation activity (Activity ID: nagaraja-act-stiffness-correlation-2024) executed by the FDA CDRH computational mechanics team using Ansys Mechanical 2023 R2 on the validated mesh ensemble. The activity included mesh sensitivity confirmation, material property traceability to certified Ti-6Al-4V coupon data, and blind prediction protocol review.",
