    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. The Test conditions factor achieves level 1 against a required level of 2; this gap is accepted because (a) the COU is restricted to static compression-bending under F1717, (b) the model influence and decision consequence are both Medium, and (c) supplementary analytical sensitivity studies confirm insensitivity of QoI predictions to plausible load-condition variations. All three primary QoIs satisfy the pre-specified quantitative acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The overall evidence package is judged sufficient to support a credibility determination of Accepted at the Medium assurance level for a Class II device.",
